---
alwaysApply: true
---

- Diorama is not a 3D editor. It is a deterministic spatial system built on a
  scene graph and command system.
- Diorama is not a DCC tool, rendering engine, Blender replacement, broad 3D
  import/export pipeline, or generic generative AI tool.
- All features must reinforce command-based architecture.
- No feature may bypass commands for persistent scene changes.
- Phase 1 prioritizes the canvas-first MVP: load starter scenes, render them,
  select nodes, inspect hierarchy, edit transforms, arrange nodes, log commands,
  undo/redo, and export JSON/R3F.
- Phase 2 agent work must compile intent into commands. Never allow direct
  hidden mutation of scene state.
- The scene graph and command system are the single source of truth. UI, export,
  eval, and MCP layers consume that state; they do not own it.
- Keep MVP scope tight. Defer modeling tools, shader graphs, multiplayer,
  animation timelines, Blender parity, and broad asset pipelines.
